metadata.name: Vršič Pass
metadata.description:
The Vršič Pass is a high mountain pass across the Julian Alps in northwestern Slovenia. With an elevation of 1,611 metres (5,285 ft)

The Slovene common noun vršič literally means 'little peak', a diminutive form of the word vrh 'peak'.
